headline.main: PROBE IS SOUGHT OF BRITISH SALES; Foreign Traders Told Eden's Note on Lease-Lend Use Was Not Satisfactory ASKS NEUTRALITY REPEAL Farrell Tells Convention Time for Appeasement Is Past -- Land Approves Move

lead_paragraph: Foreign traders were called upon here yesterday to ask the American Government to give them "the support which national welfare deserves" in demanding a satisfactory explanation of the export operations of the British Government and British exporters.
abstract: S on Neutrality Act repeal, Natl Foreign Trade Conv
